K-Means Clustering

Make some data with clusters.

set.seed(101)
x = matrix(rnorm(100 *2), 100, 2)
xmean = matrix(rnorm(8, sd = 4), 4, 2)
which = sample(1:4, 100, replace = T)
x = x + xmean[which,]

plot(x, col = which, pch = 20)

‘kmeans’ algorithm

km.out = kmeans(x, 4, nstart = 15)
km.out
## K-means clustering with 4 clusters of sizes 32, 28, 20, 20

plot(x, col = km.out$cluster, cex = 2, pch = 1, lwd = 2)
points(x, col = c(4, 3, 2, 1)[which], pch = 19)

Hierarchical Clustering

hc.complete = hclust(dist(x), method = "complete")
plot(hc.complete, main = "cluster dendrogram - complete")

hc.single = hclust(dist(x), method = "single")
plot(hc.single, main = "cluster dendrogram - single")

hc.average = hclust(dist(x), method = "average")
plot(hc.average, main = "cluster dendrogram - average")

hc.cut = cutree(hc.complete, 4)
table(hc.cut, which)
##       which
## hc.cut  1  2  3  4
##      1  0 28  0  0
##      2  1  0  0 20
##      3 31  0  0  0
##      4  0  0 20  0
table(hc.cut, km.out$cluster)
##       
## hc.cut  1  2  3  4
##      1  0 28  0  0
##      2  1  0  0 20
##      3 31  0  0  0
##      4  0  0 20  0
plot(hc.complete, labels = which)
